        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 5:05PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 505 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Montross, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Montross around 510 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Currioman Landing,
Singerly, Mount Holly, Erica, Piney Grove, Kremlin, Foneswood, and
Templeman.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for east central
Virginia.</instruction>
